  "texts": [
    "Finally, personal data could be provided as input/training data.",
    "All the above from this category could be personal data or mixt data.",
    "Whether provided by a user or by the developer of the AI system, this automatically falls under data privacy protection.",
    "When it comes to the developer, certain filters could be put in place for assuring that no personal data processing will be performed.",
    "However, the content provided by the user when using conversational AI might not be filtered easily (Business & Human Rights Centre, 2023) and neither the collection of personal data prevented (Ericsson, 2022)."
